@petr-ujezdsky Thanks for the feedback. Naturally I would prefer to use the built-in health check functionality. Unfortunately, few containers actually implement it. So it might be possible in _some_ situations, but definitely not all.

I'll look into your `exec` workaround, but imho that is even dirtier ;).

Having `podman logs` behave like it says in the documentation is desirable in any case.
